headline.print_headline: SEC Scores Partial Win in Insider Trading Case Over 2009 Sanofi Deal
headline.main: SEC Scores Partial Win in Insider Trading Case Over 2009 Sanofi Deal

lead_paragraph: Federal securities regulators have won a partial victory against two brothers accused of trading on inside information in 2009 about French pharmaceutical company Sanofi's plan to buy a Tennessee-based company.
